<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">29</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">2</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Mar 1 2009</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">509</span> - <span property="pageEnd">523</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19325062/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">19325062</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2009.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Mar 1 2009</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.292085128">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keyword</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=DCIS+%3D+ductal+carcinoma+in+situ&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">DCIS = ductal carcinoma in situ</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">The anatomy of the nipple-areolar complex is reviewed and detailed descriptions are provided of normal variants and benign and malignant processes that may be seen at physical examination and at mammography, US, and MR imaging with diagnostically specific techniques.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><s